.TH "amdgpu_device_ip_is_idle" 9 "amdgpu_device_ip_is_idle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
amdgpu_device_ip_is_idle \- is the hardware IP idle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" amdgpu_device_ip_is_idle
.BI "(struct amdgpu_device *adev "  ","
.BI "enum amd_ip_block_type block_type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adev" 12
amdgpu_device pointer
.IP "block_type" 12
Type of hardware IP (SMU, GFX, UVD, etc.)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Check if the hardware IP is idle or not.
Returns true if it the IP is idle, false if not.
